data.meta_desc: During World War II, the U.S. Marines selected 29 Navajo men, who later came to be known as the Navajo Code Talkers, to create a code based on the complex and unwritten Navajo language. The system was so efficient that it enabled Code Talkers to translate three lines of a English in more 20 seconds and not 30 minute as was common at that time. Even at the end of the war, the Navajo Code remained unbroken by the enemy forces. Memes.
